<%# Locals: event.
    Phase 8 — Badge Design & Printing (requirement.md §3.6, §5.5). Designing/editing a badge still
    happens on Admin::BadgesController#edit's own full page — a GrapesJS canvas genuinely doesn't
    fit in a wizard step panel — but any badge *already* designed for this event shows right here
    now (the same table admin/badges/index.html.erb itself renders, extracted to
    admin/badges/_badges_table), not just a "go look elsewhere" button. A tenant who's already
    designed a badge shouldn't have to leave the wizard to find out whether they have — that gap
    (leaving this step to just check) was the actual reported problem, not the editor itself
    needing to move. %>
<% badges = event.badges.includes(:ticket_category).order(:ticket_category_id) %>

<div class="card">
  <%# "New Badge" moved into the card header, next to the section's own name, rather than a
      separate row above the card — same shape admin/badges/index.html.erb's own page header
      already uses for this exact button. Still only shown once there's at least one badge already
      (the empty-state's own "Design a badge" CTA inside the table partial covers the zero-badges
      case — a second button for the same action would be redundant). %>
  <div class="card-header d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center">
    <span class="fw-semibold">Badges</span>
    <% if badges.any? %>
      <%= link_to "New Badge", new_admin_event_badge_path(event), class: "btn btn-m btn-primary" %>
    <% end %>
  </div>
  <div class="card-body">
    <%= render "admin/badges/badges_table", event: event, badges: badges %>
  </div>
</div>
